This Privacy Policy applies to the SGO Game App (referred to as the "Application") for mobile devices, created by SGO Developer (referred to as the "Service Provider"). The Application is provided as a free service and is intended for use "AS IS."

Information Collection and Use
The Application collects information when you download and use it. This may include:

Your device's Internet Protocol (IP) address.
Details about the pages you visit within the Application, including the time, date, and duration of your visits.
The time spent using the Application.
The operating system of your mobile device.
The Application does not collect precise location data from your device.

The Service Provider may use the information you provide to:

Contact you with important updates, notices, or marketing promotions.
Improve the functionality and experience of the Application.
Any personally identifiable information collected will be retained and used as described in this Privacy Policy.

Third-Party Access
The Application may transmit aggregated and anonymized data to external services to improve the Application and related services.

The Application also uses third-party services that may collect information in accordance with their own Privacy Policies. Below are the links to the Privacy Policies of third-party services utilized by the Application:

Google Play Services
AdMob
The Service Provider may share collected information in the following circumstances:

As Required by Law: To comply with legal obligations, such as subpoenas or similar legal processes.
For Protection: When disclosure is necessary to protect the rights, safety, or property of users or others, or to investigate fraud.
With Trusted Service Providers: With third-party providers who act on behalf of the Service Provider, under agreements that ensure the confidentiality and appropriate use of your information.
Opt-Out Rights
You can stop all data collection by uninstalling the Application. To uninstall, use the standard processes available on your device or through the app marketplace where the Application was downloaded.

Data Retention Policy
The Service Provider retains user-provided data for as long as you use the Application and for a reasonable time thereafter.

To request the deletion of any data you have provided, please contact the Service Provider at sgodeveloper827@gmail.com. Your request will be addressed promptly.

Children's Privacy
The Application is not intended for children under 13 years of age, and the Service Provider does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

If it is discovered that a child under 13 has provided personal information, the Service Provider will immediately delete this information from its servers.

If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided personal information, please contact the Service Provider at sgodeveloper827@gmail.com to take the necessary action.

Security
The Service Provider prioritizes the confidentiality of your information and employs physical, electronic, and procedural safeguards to protect the data it processes and maintains.

However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet or method of electronic storage is completely secure. While the Service Provider strives to protect your information, absolute security cannot be guaranteed.

Changes to This Privacy Policy
This Privacy Policy may be updated periodically. The Service Provider will notify users of changes by updating this page with the revised Privacy Policy.

You are encouraged to review this Privacy Policy regularly, as continued use of the Application constitutes your acceptance of any changes.

Your Consent
By using the Application, you consent to the collection, use, and processing of your information as described in this Privacy Policy, including any amendments.

Contact Us
If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or the handling of your information, please contact the Service Provider at sgodeveloper827@gmail.com.

Effective Date: January 11, 2025
